Taking $ABC$ to be the base of pyramid $ABCH$, the height is $HD$.  Therefore, the volume of pyramid $ABCH$ is $$\frac{[ABC](HD)}{3}.$$We are given that this volume equals 20, so we have \[{[ABC]\cdot HD}=60.\]The volume of prism $ABCDEFGH$ is the product of area of $ABCD$ and the height of the prism, which equals $HD$.   The area of $ABC$ is half the area of rectangle $ABCD$, so we have  \begin{align*}
\text{Volume of }ABCDEFGH &= ([ABCD])(HD) \\
&= 2([ABC])(HD) \\
&= \boxed{120}.\end{align*}

