label("{\tiny r}",(15,2),N);
label("{\tiny r}",(16.7,2.4),N);
label("{\tiny 5}",(19,0),S);
label("{\tiny 5-r}",(16.5,0),S);
label("{\tiny 5-r}",(18.2,1.7),E);
label("{\tiny 12}",(14,12),W);
label("{\tiny 12-r}",(14,7),W);
label("{\tiny 12-r}",(15.67,8),E);
[/asy]



To determine the radius $r$ of the inscribed circle notice that the hypotenuse of the triangle is \[
(12-r) + (5-r) = 13\]so $r=2$.


So the center of the inscribed circle is $(2,2)$, and the distance between the two centers is \[
\sqrt{\displaystyle\left( \frac{5}{2} -2\displaystyle\right)^{2}+(6-2)^{2}}= \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{65}}{2}}.
\]

problem:
In the figure, point $A$ is the center of the circle, the measure of angle $RAS$ is 74 degrees, and the measure of angle $RTB$ is 28 degrees. What is the measure of minor arc $BR$, in degrees? [asy]
